  "texts": [
    "By automating repetitive tasks and reducing manual intervention, actuaries can focus on higher-value activities, such as strategic planning, oversight, and risk management.",
    "Furthermore, AI-powered tools and technology stacks can help actuaries make more informed decisions by providing real-time insights and predictive analytics.",
    "As industries (where actuaries have traditionally played a role) embrace the use of AI and advanced data science techniques, should actuaries be considered the specialists in this area, or should they be users and interpreters of output from these tools, produced by other specialists?",
    "The Actuaries' Code (IFoA, 2019), Principle 2, under Competence and Care, notes that \"[m] embers must consider whether input from other professionals or specialists is necessary to assure the relevance and quality of work and, where necessary, either seek it themselves or advise the user to do so, as appropriate\".",
    "Should actuaries produce, interpret, use, and risk manage these systems, or should they only perform a subset of these duties?"
  ],
